org.elkoserver.foundation.timer

Class Timeout

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.elkoserver.foundation.timer.Timeout

  • public class Timeout
extends Object
    Object representing a scheduled timeout event. Timeouts can only be created by calling the after() method on a Timer instance.
    See Also:
    TimeoutNoticer

    • Method Detail

      • cancel

        public boolean cancel()
        Cancels this timeout. Note, however, that although a Timeout can be cancelled, there is no guarantee that it has not already occured by the time it is cancelled.
        Returns:
        true if cancellation was successful, false if it wasn't.
